					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Fragment of a slab excavated behind the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>The date portion of the record is damaged. However, on the basis of palaeography, it may be assigned to the 16th century.</p>						

						<p>Fragment. It seems to register a gift of land by Rāmānāyaniṅgāru in the presence of god Tiruveṅgaḷanātha. The details regarding donee's name is not clear.</p>						

						</summary>
